es that he will get past. I think he\u2019s progressed very well.\"\n\nMichigan State needs Lewerke to progress more as a redshirt sophomore. The program is in a pivotal year. Last year's 3-9 season came just one year after an appearance in the College Football Playoff. Penn State's Trace McSorley, Ohio State's J.T. Barrett and Michigan's Wilton Speight all return to their respective programs in 2017.\n\nIf Michigan State is going to bounce back on the field in 2017, then Lewerke will have to show signs of that next-level play that helped make the program successful in the past. He flashed that on the opening drive.\n\nLewerke is \"the guy right now.\" He'll have to be even better in the fall.\n\n\"Every time he takes a snap in an environment where there are people there or something of that nature he\u2019s going to get better and better and better.,\" Dantonio said. \"There\u2019s always a little bit of a learning curve, but he\u2019s a good player.\u201d", 
