        "body2": "CLYDE, Texas (KRBC) - His workshop doesn't have elves, and he doesn't answer to Claus or Cringle, but that hasn't stopped this Clyde resident from doing some fairly jolly work.\n\n\"In the last two or three months I've made over 250 toys, by myself, just me,\" commented Tom Watson.\n\nTom has spent several years crafting several thousand wooden toys.\n\nThese toys, however, aren't for sale, they're for local kids going through trying times.\n\n\"I'm not in this as a business, this is a hobby, it's a way for me to give back. I'm a 67 going on 68-year-old, disabled Vietnam veteran, and it kind of helps me.\"\n\nHe started in Arizona where he donated his creations to local relief groups.\n\nWhen he packed up shop and moved to Clyde he started his operation all over again.\n\n\"I started looking for organizations that would like donations.\"\n\nTom's constant goal is to bring a sense of calm to the children who receive one of his toys.\n\nEach of those toys comes with a guarantee, if a kids breaks the toy, \"I will give you two to replace it,\" finished Tom\n\nOn top of all that Tom says toy making is something he plans to do until he can do it no longer.", 
